<p>Hi Emil,</p>
<p>The beauty of mymind is that it naturally fits into your life and workflow.</p>
<p>Especially when you’re <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Fc-DwH2V79U&t=2s" target="_blank" style="color: #FF5924;"><strong>using the mobile app.</strong></a></p>
<img src="https://carbon-media.accelerator.net/00000000001/g0OL0EDobIZflKJ9yGTujj;870x540.png?auto=webp" width="960" height="463" style="max-width:100%;height:auto;"/>
<p>Once you have the iOS or Android app on your phone, you can share a link, image or post to your mind just like you’d share anything else.</p>
<p>➺ <a href="https://apps.apple.com/us/app/mymind-extend-your-mind/id1520332347" target="_blank" style="color: #FF5924;">Download the iPhone app here</a><br />
➺ <a href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.mymind.access&hl=en_US&gl=US" target="_blank" style="color: #FF5924;">Download the Android app here</a></p>
<p>Tap the “share” option (on a website, social media, your camera roll, wherever) to save something straight to your mind. It works the same way as you would share anything else.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>Share any link to save it from mobile</strong></p>
<img src="https://carbon-media.accelerator.net/00000000001/1g4IUCZSRFwdRx2wSkFeQl;870x540.png?auto=webp" width="960" height="463" style="max-width:100%;height:auto;"/>
<p>To save a website, hit the browser share icon on iOS, or the [...] icon on Android, then tap Share. Now select the mymind app in the share panel.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>Highlight &amp; share text to save highlights or quotes</strong></p>
<img src="https://carbon-media.accelerator.net/00000000001/lAtWmWWe4bpdmC7uOZaWhb;870x540.png?auto=webp" width="960" height="463" style="max-width:100%;height:auto;"/>
<p>If you’re reading something interesting on mobile (this email, for example) simply highlight the text you want to save and click “Share” when the option appears. Select mymind from the share panel and you’re done. It’s in your mind.</p>
<p>✱ <em>Pro tip: Make mymind a &quot;Favorite&quot;in your share panel, so it's always near the top when you hit share.</em></p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>It works the same way for anything you want to save to your mind from your phone:</strong></p>
<p>✓ Photos from your Camera Roll<br />
✓ A tweet, or an image that’s part of a tweet<br />
✓ An image from an article or search<br />
✓ A screenshot from your phone<br />
✓ Anything you’d like to save</p>
<p>If you’re on your phone now, <a href="https://apps.apple.com/us/app/mymind-extend-your-mind/id1520332347" target="_blank" style="color: #FF5924;">install the iPhone app here</a> or the <a href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.mymind.access&hl=en_US&gl=US" target="_blank" style="color: #FF5924;">Android app right here</a>. Then your mind is only a tap away, no matter where you are.</p>
<p> </p>
<p>Questions? Wondering how to make that beautiful mymind icon show up in your share panel? Want to chat about the weather? Reply here and we'll talk.</p>


